<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of regulation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi seadus reguleerib isikule ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi andmise korda ja tingimusi ning isikule ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi andmisel tekkivaid suhteid tervishoiuasutustega; s&auml;testab riigi ja kohaliku omavalitsuse kohustused ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi korraldamisel ning isiku &otilde;igused ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi saamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>The Mental Health Act regulates the procedure and conditions for provision of psychiatric care and the relationships with health care institutions which arise from the provision of psychiatric care, provides the duties of the state and local governments in the organisation of psychiatric care, and provides the rights of persons in receiving psychiatric care. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevas seaduses kasutatakse m&otilde;isteid j&auml;rgmises t&auml;henduses: </eesti>
<inglise>In this Act, the following definitions are used: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;ire - kehtivale rahvusvahelisele ps&uuml;&uuml;hika- ja k&auml;itumish&auml;irete klassifikatsioonile vastav ps&uuml;&uuml;hiline seisund v&otilde;i k&auml;itumish&auml;ire; </eesti>
<inglise>1) "mental disorder" means a mental state or behavioural disorder according to the current international classification of mental and behavioural disorders; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ps&uuml;hhiaatriline abi - ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irete diagnostika, ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irega isiku ravi ja taastusabi ning ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;ireid ennetav tegevus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) "psychiatric care" means diagnosis of mental disorders, treatment and rehabilitation of persons with mental disorders and anything done for the prevention of mental disorders; </inglise>
<eesti>3) raviprotsess - isiku uurimise, diagnoosimise, ravimise ja taastusabiga seotud tegevus, mis h&otilde;lmab suhteid patsiendi ja arsti ning teiste ravimisele kaasatud isikute, raviasutuste ja haigekassaga; </eesti>
<inglise>3) "treatment setting" means activities related to assessment, diagnosis, treatment and rehabilitation of persons which includes relationships between patients and doctors and other persons, health care institutions and the health insurance fund involved in the treatment; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irega isiku taastusabi - tegevus ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irega isiku sotsiaalse toimetulekuv&otilde;ime taastamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) "rehabilitation of a person with a mental disorder" means anything done for restoring the social coping skills of a person with a mental disorder; </inglise>
<eesti>5) teadev n&otilde;usolek - n&otilde;usolek, mille andmisel isik on v&otilde;imeline aru saama n&otilde;usoleku olemusest ja selle andmise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise tagaj&auml;rgedest. </eesti>
<inglise>5) "informed consent" means consent given where the person is capable of understanding the meaning of consent and the consequences of granting or refusing consent. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi vabatahtlikkus </eesti>
<inglise>Voluntary nature of psychiatric care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist abi antakse vaba tahte avalduse alusel, s.t. isiku soovil v&otilde;i teadval n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Psychiatric care is provided on a voluntary basis, that is, at the request or with the informed consent of a person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teov&otilde;imetule isikule antakse ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist abi tema seadusliku esindaja soovil v&otilde;i n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Psychiatric care is provided to a person without active legal capacity at the request or with the consent of his or her legal representative. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irega isiku ravi ilma tema teadva n&otilde;usolekuta v&otilde;i seadusliku esindaja n&otilde;usolekuta on lubatud ainult k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvides 11 ja 17 s&auml;testatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The treatment of a person with a mental disorder without his or her informed consent or the consent of his or her legal representative is permitted only in the cases provided for in &sect;&sect; 11 and 17 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Isiku &otilde;igused ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi saamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of person while receiving psychiatric care </inglise>
<eesti>Isikul on ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi saamisel &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>While receiving psychiatric care, a person has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) saada ravi ja p&otilde;etust v&otilde;rdsel alusel muude haigetega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) receive treatment and nursing on equal grounds with other patients; </inglise>
<eesti>2) saada teavet oma ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;ire ja kasutatavate ravi- ning diagnostikameetodite kohta ja tutvuda temasse puutuvate ravidokumentidega, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui see v&otilde;ib osutuda kahjulikuks tema vaimsele tervisele v&otilde;i teiste isikute julgeolekule. Otsuse teabe edastamise kohta teeb ja annab &otilde;iguse tutvuda ravidokumentidega tema raviarst, kes teeb sellekohase kande tema ravidokumenti; </eesti>
<inglise>2) receive information on his or her mental disorder, methods of treatment and diagnosis being used, and review his or her medical file, except if this may be harmful to his or her mental health or the safety of others. The decision to disclose information or grant the right to examine the medical file is made by the attending physician of the patient and the attending physician shall make a corresponding entry in the medical file of the person; </inglise>
<eesti>3) keelduda ps&uuml;hhiaatrilistest uuringutest ja ravist v&otilde;i neid katkestada, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvides 11, 15, 16 ja 17 s&auml;testatud juhtudel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) refuse or discontinue psychiatric assessment or treatment, except in the cases provided for in &sect;&sect; 11, 15, 16 and 17 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kahju h&uuml;vitamisele ravi- v&otilde;i p&otilde;etusvigadest p&otilde;hjustatud kahju korral. </eesti>
<inglise>4) compensation for damage in the case of damage caused by errors in treatment or nursing. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irete diagnostika ja ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irega isiku ravi </eesti>
<inglise>Diagnosis of mental disorders and treatment of persons with mental disorders </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arst on ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irete diagnoosimisel ja ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi andmisel s&otilde;ltumatu ning juhindub arstiteadusest, arstieetikast, seadustest ja muudest &otilde;igusaktidest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Physicians are independent in the diagnosis of mental disorders and provision of psychiatric care, and are guided by medical science, the medical code of ethics, laws and other legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist ravi ja diagnoosi puudutav teave on isiku eraelu saladus ja selle edastamine v&auml;ljaspoole raviprotsessi on lubatud ainult isiku enda v&otilde;i tema seadusliku esindaja kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul, samuti juurdlusorgani, politsei, prokuratuuri v&otilde;i kohtu seadusest tuleneva n&otilde;ude alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Information concerning psychiatric treatment and diagnosis is confidential information and disclosure thereof outside the treatment setting is permitted only with the written consent of the person or his or her legal representative, or at the request, pursuant to law, of an investigative body, the police, the Prosecutor's Office or the courts. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irega isiku raviarst ei ole kohustatud andma kellelegi &uuml;tlusi isiku eraelu kohta, mida ta sai teada oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The attending physician of a person with a mental disorder is not required to make any statements to any person regarding confidential information of which the physician becomes aware in the course of his or her duties. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of Psychiatric Care </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi korraldamise &uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General principles of organisation of psychiatric care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abiga tagatakse raviprotsessis ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irega isikule j&auml;rjepidev ja sotsiaalministri poolt kehtestatud standarditele vastav ravi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Psychiatric care provides persons with mental disorders with treatment which is continuous and in accordance with the standards established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist abi annavad sellekohase tegevusloaga raviasutused, arstid ja muud spetsialistid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Psychiatric care is provided by health care institutions, physicians and other specialists with appropriate activity licences. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;ldarst annab ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist abi oma p&auml;devuse piires. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) General practitioners provide psychiatric care within the limits of their competence. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ps&uuml;hhiaatriline eriarstiabi korraldatakse kohaliku omavalitsuse ja riigi tasandil. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Specialised psychiatric care is organised at the local government and state levels. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi andmisel v&auml;lditakse v&otilde;imaluse korral isiku eemaldamist harjumusp&auml;rasest elukeskkonnast. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If possible, the removal of persons from familiar surroundings is avoided in the provision of psychiatric care. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist haiglaravi rakendatakse juhul, kui isiku tervise seisundist l&auml;htuvalt ei ole haiglav&auml;line abi piisavalt t&otilde;hus v&otilde;i kui isik on temal esineva ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;ire t&otilde;ttu muutunud endale v&otilde;i teistele ohtlikuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A person is placed in inpatient psychiatric treatment if outpatient care is not sufficiently effective due to the state of health of the person or if the person becomes dangerous to himself or herself or others due to a mental disorder. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi &uuml;lesanded ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi korraldamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of state in organisation of psychiatric care </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi tasandil korraldab ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist abi Sotsiaalministeerium, kelle &uuml;lesanded t&auml;iendavalt tervishoiukorralduse seaduses (RT I 1994, 10, 133; 1995, 57, 978; 1997, 86, 1462; 1999, 18, 305; 23, 351) s&auml;testatule on: </eesti>
<inglise>At the state level, psychiatric care is organised by the Ministry of Social Affairs, whose duties, in addition to the duties prescribed in the Health Care Administration Act (RT I 1994, 10, 133; 1995, 57, 978; 1997, 86, 1462; 1999, 18, 305; 23, 351), are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kohtu poolt ps&uuml;hhiaatriahaiglasse paigutatud isikute ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise ravi korraldamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) organisation of psychiatric treatment for persons committed to psychiatric hospitals by the courts; </inglise>
<eesti>2) erihooldekodudes antava ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi korraldamine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) organisation of psychiatric care provided in special care homes; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;ireid ennetava tegevuse korraldamine. </eesti>
<inglise>3) organisation of activities for prevention of mental disorders. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;lesanded ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi korraldamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of local governments in organisation of psychiatric care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kohaliku omavalitsuse tasandil korraldab ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist abi valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus koosk&otilde;lastatult maavanemaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) At the local government level, psychiatric care shall be organised by the rural municipality government or city government in concordance with the county governor. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 50, 284) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.05.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 50, 284) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohalik omavalitsus tagab ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi kiirabina, haiglav&auml;lise, haigla- ja taastusabina. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Local governments shall provide psychiatric care through emergency medical aid, outpatient care, inpatient care and rehabilitation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kohalik omavalitsus korraldab ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist abi k&auml;esoleva seaduse n&otilde;uete kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Local governments shall organise psychiatric care pursuant to the requirements of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kohalik omavalitsus tagab v&auml;ltimatu ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmamata isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Local governments shall ensure emergency psychiatric care to persons who are not covered by health insurance. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi seos sotsiaalhoolekandega </eesti>
<inglise>Inclusion of psychiatric care in social welfare </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kohalik omavalitsus tagab ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irega isikule sotsiaalteenuste k&auml;ttesaadavuse ja nende sidumise ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Local governments shall ensure that social services are accessible for persons with mental disorders and include the provision of psychiatric care. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohalik omavalitsus korraldab ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;ire t&otilde;ttu vaeguriks tunnistatud isiku tervise seisundile vastava hooldamise, mis toimub sotsiaalhoolekande seadusega (RT I 1995, 21, 323; 1996, 49, 953; 1997; 35, 538; 77, 1309; 2000, 33, 198) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Local governments shall ensure that persons declared to be disabled due to a mental disorder are provided with care which is appropriate to their state of health, pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Social Welfare Act (RT I 1995, 21, 323; 1996, 49, 953; 1997, 35, 538; 77, 1309; 2000, 33, 198). </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;ltimatu ps&uuml;hhiaatriline abi </eesti>
<inglise>Emergency Psychiatric Care </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;ltimatu ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi andmise &uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General principles of provision of emergency psychiatric care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&otilde;igile Eesti territooriumil viibivatele isikutele tagatakse v&auml;ltimatu ps&uuml;hhiaatriline abi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) All persons in the territory of Estonia are provided with emergency psychiatric care. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&auml;ltimatut ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist abi saab ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irega isik vaba tahte avalduse alusel, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 11 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Persons with mental disorders receive emergency psychiatric care on a voluntary basis, except in the cases provided for in subsection 11 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;ltimatu ps&uuml;hhiaatriline abi tagatakse ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irete korral, kus abita j&auml;tmine ohustab otseselt isiku elu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Emergency psychiatric care is provided in the case of mental disorders where failure to provide care endangers the life of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) V&auml;ltimatut ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist abi antakse isiku tervise seisundist l&auml;htuvalt kiirabi, haiglav&auml;lise v&otilde;i haiglaabi korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Emergency psychiatric care is provided according to the state of health of a person through emergency medical aid, outpatient care or inpatient care. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Tahtest olenematu v&auml;ltimatu ps&uuml;hhiaatriline abi </eesti>
<inglise>Involuntary emergency psychiatric care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik v&otilde;etakse tema enda v&otilde;i tema seadusliku esindaja n&otilde;usolekuta v&auml;ltimatu ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi korras ravile haigla ps&uuml;hhiaatriaosakonda v&otilde;i j&auml;tkatakse ravi, tema tahtest olenemata, ainult j&auml;rgmiste asjaolude koosesinemise korral: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person is admitted to the psychiatric department of a hospital for emergency psychiatric care without the consent of the person or his or her legal representative, or the treatment of a person is continued regardless of his or her wishes only if all of the following circumstances exist: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isikul on raske ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;ire, mis piirab tema v&otilde;imet oma k&auml;itumisest aru saada v&otilde;i seda juhtida; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the person has a severe mental disorder which restricts his or her ability to understand or control his or her behaviour; </inglise>
<eesti>2) haiglaravita j&auml;tmisel ohustab isik ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;ire t&otilde;ttu iseenda v&otilde;i teiste elu, tervist v&otilde;i julgeolekut; </eesti>
<inglise>2) without inpatient treatment, the person endangers the life, health or safety of himself or herself or others due to a mental disorder; and </inglise>
<eesti>3) muu ps&uuml;hhiaatriline abi ei ole k&uuml;llaldane. </eesti>
<inglise>3) other psychiatric care is not sufficient. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Otsuse isik ravile v&otilde;tta teeb haigla ps&uuml;hhiaatriaosakonna arst vajaduse ilmnemisel viivitamata p&auml;rast isiku arstlikku l&auml;bivaatust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If after carrying out a medical examination of a person the need to admit the person for treatment becomes evident, a physician of the psychiatric department of a hospital shall promptly make such decision. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus vormistatakse sotsiaalministri kehtestatud korra kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>Such decisions shall be documented pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuse vormistamise aeg loetakse tahtest olenematu haiglaravi alguseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The date of documenting a decision is deemed to be the commencement of involuntary inpatient treatment. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud asjaoludel ravil viibiv isik ei v&otilde;i katkestada uuringuid ja ravi ega lahkuda haigla ps&uuml;hhiaatriaosakonnast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Persons who are in treatment in the circumstances provided for in subsection (1) of this section shall not discontinue assessment or treatment or leave the psychiatric department of the hospital. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Tahtest olenematut v&auml;ltimatut ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist abi vajava isiku haiglasse paigutamise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for hospitalization of persons in need of involuntary emergency psychiatric care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 11 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud asjaoludel toimetatakse isik haigla ps&uuml;hhiaatriaosakonda kiirabi, politsei, l&auml;hedaste v&otilde;i muude isikute poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the circumstances provided for in subsection 11 (1) of this Act, a person is taken to the psychiatric department of a hospital by emergency medical staff, police, a person close to him or her, or another person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 11 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud asjaoludel ja arsti kirjaliku taotluse alusel abistab politsei meditsiinit&ouml;&ouml;tajaid isiku kinnipidamisel, arstlikul l&auml;bivaatusel ja haigla ps&uuml;hhiaatriaosakonda toimetamisel ning tagab isiku vara ajutise kaitse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the circumstances provided for in subsection 11 (1) of this Act and on the basis of a written request of a physician, the police shall aid medical staff in detaining, carrying out medical examinations on and transferring a person to the psychiatric department of a hospital, and ensure temporary protection of the property of such person. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tahtest olenematu v&auml;ltimatu ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise ravi (edaspidi - tahtest olenematu ravi) rakendamise otsusest teavitab arst isikut koheselt ja tema l&auml;hedast inimest v&otilde;i seaduslikku esindajat 72 tunni jooksul otsuse vormistamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A physician shall immediately inform a person of a decision to place the person in involuntary emergency psychiatric treatment (hereinafter involuntary treatment) and inform a person close to him or her, or his or her legal representative within seventy-two hours of documenting the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tahtest olenematu ravi rakendamisel on isiku l&auml;hedasel inimesel ja seaduslikul esindajal v&otilde;i nende poolt valitud arstil v&otilde;i advokaadil &otilde;igus l&uuml;hiajaliselt kohtuda tahtest olenematule ravile paigutatud isikuga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon placing a person in involuntary treatment, a person close to or legal representative of the person or a physician or lawyer of their choice have the right to meet briefly with the person placed in involuntary treatment. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtumise kestuse otsustab raviarst, l&auml;htudes ravile paigutatud isiku tervise seisundist. </eesti>
<inglise>The duration of such meeting shall be decided by the attending physician based on the state of health of the person placed in treatment. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui arstil puudub teave isiku l&auml;hedase inimese v&otilde;i seadusliku esindaja olemasolu ja nende asukoha kohta, teavitab ta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 toodud t&auml;htaja jooksul tahtest olenematu ravi rakendamisest isiku elukohaj&auml;rgset kohalikku omavalitsust. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a physician has no information regarding the existence or address of a person close to or legal representative of the person, the physician shall inform the local government of the residence of the person that the person has been placed in involuntary treatment within the term specified in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Tahtest olenematu ravi kontrollimine </eesti>
<inglise>Review of involuntary treatment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Haigla pea- v&otilde;i &uuml;lemarst tagab tahtest olenematult ravile v&otilde;etud isiku arstliku l&auml;bivaatuse kahe ps&uuml;hhiaatri poolt 48 tunni jooksul haiglaravi algusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The chief doctor of a hospital shall ensure that two psychiatrists carry out a medical examination of a person admitted for involuntary treatment within forty-eight hours after commencement of inpatient treatment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui &uuml;ks v&otilde;i m&otilde;lemad ps&uuml;hhiaatrid tunnistavad ravile v&otilde;tmise v&otilde;i ravi j&auml;tkamise k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 11 l&otilde;ike 1 alusel p&otilde;hjendamatuks ning isik ei ole n&otilde;us j&auml;&auml;ma ravile haigla ps&uuml;hhiaatriaosakonda, v&otilde;ib ta haiglast koheselt lahkuda. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If one or both of the psychiatrists declare the admission for treatment or continuation of treatment pursuant to subsection 11 (1) of this Act to be unjustified and the person does not consent to remain in treatment in the psychiatric department of the hospital, the person may immediately leave the hospital. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui m&otilde;lemad ps&uuml;hhiaatrid tunnistavad isiku ravile v&otilde;tmise v&otilde;i ravi j&auml;tkamise k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 11 l&otilde;ike 1 alusel p&otilde;hjendatuks, j&auml;etakse isik tahtest olenematule ravile kuni 14 p&auml;evaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If both psychiatrists declare the admission for treatment or continuation of treatment of the person pursuant to subsection 11 (1) of this Act to be justified, the person shall be kept in involuntary treatment for up to fourteen days. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Isiku tahtest olenematu ravi haigla ps&uuml;hhiaatriaosakonnas v&otilde;ib kesta &uuml;le 14 p&auml;eva ainult kohtu loal, mille annab halduskohus haigla pea- v&otilde;i &uuml;lemarsti kirjaliku taotluse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Involuntary treatment of a person in the psychiatric department of a hospital may continue for more than fourteen days only with the authorisation of a court which is issued by an administrative court on the basis of a written application of the chief doctor of the hospital. </inglise>
<eesti>Halduskohtunik vaatab l&auml;bi tahtest olenematuks raviks loa andmise taotluse ja otsustab loa andmise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise viivitamata, kohtuistungit korraldamata. </eesti>
<inglise>An administrative court judge shall review an application for authorisation of involuntary treatment and promptly decide whether to grant or deny authorisation, without a court hearing. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Loa isiku tahtest olenematuks raviks v&otilde;ib halduskohtunik anda esimesel korral kuni 30 p&auml;evaks, alates taotluse kohtusse saabumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) On the first occasion, an administrative court judge may grant authorisation for involuntary treatment of a person for up to thirty days as of the date of receipt of the application by the court. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;rgnevatel kordadel v&otilde;ib halduskohtunik pikendada luba isiku tahtest olenematuks raviks kuni 90 p&auml;evaks, alates eelmise korra l&otilde;ppemisele j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>On subsequent occasions, an administrative court judge may extend the authorisation for involuntary treatment of a person for up to ninety days as of the day following the end of the previous period. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui halduskohtunik keeldub loa andmisest v&otilde;i pikendamisest isiku tahtest olenematuks raviks v&otilde;i t&uuml;histab antud loa, v&otilde;ib isik haiglast koheselt lahkuda v&otilde;i j&auml;tkata ravi vaba tahte alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If an administrative court judge refuses to grant or extend authorisation for involuntary treatment of a person or revokes an authorisation, the person may immediately leave the hospital or continue treatment voluntarily. </inglise>
<eesti>(6 (1)) Isiku tahtest olenematuks v&auml;ltimatuks ps&uuml;hhiaatriliseks raviks antud loa t&uuml;histab halduskohtunik j&auml;relevalvet teostava ametniku protesti v&otilde;i ravil viibiva isiku abikaasa, seadusliku esindaja v&otilde;i l&auml;hisugulaste taotluse alusel, olles &auml;ra kuulanud haigla pea- v&otilde;i &uuml;lemarsti v&otilde;i tema kohuseid t&auml;itva selleks volitatud arsti seletuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(6 (1)) An administrative court judge shall revoke an authorisation for involuntary treatment of a person on the basis of a protest of the official exercising supervision or an application of the spouse, legal representative or a close relative of the person in treatment, having heard the explanation of the chief doctor of the hospital or of a doctor performing the duties of the chief doctor who has been authorised to provide the explanation. </inglise>
<eesti>Vajadusel v&otilde;ib halduskohtunik m&auml;&auml;rata ravil viibivale isikule kohtups&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiisi. </eesti>
<inglise>If necessary, an administrative court judge may order a forensic psychiatric examination of the person in treatment. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.02.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 31, 425; 30.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 53, 309) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.02.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 31, 425, 967; 30.05.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 1999, 2001, 53) </inglise>
<eesti>(6 (2)) Loa andmine, pikendamine ja t&uuml;histamine isiku tahtest olenematuks v&auml;ltimatuks ps&uuml;hhiaatriliseks raviks otsustatakse halduskohtumenetluse seadustiku haldustoiminguks loa andmise s&auml;tete j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(6 (2)) The grant, extension and revocation of an authorisation for involuntary emergency psychiatric treatment of a person shall be decided pursuant to the provisions of the Code of Administrative Court Procedure concerning the grant of permission for administrative acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.02.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 31, 425) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.02.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 31, 425) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui tahtest olenematu ravi k&auml;igus langeb &auml;ra v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks paragrahv 11 l&otilde;ikes 1 toodud asjaolu, l&otilde;petatakse kahe ps&uuml;hhiaatri otsusel tahtest olenematu ravi ja isik v&otilde;ib haiglast koheselt lahkuda v&otilde;i j&auml;tkata ravi vaba tahte avalduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If even one of the circumstances specified in subsection 11 (1) ceases to exist during involuntary treatment, the involuntary treatment shall be discontinued on the basis of a decision of two psychiatrists, and the person may immediately leave the hospital or continue treatment voluntarily. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ravi oli antud kohtu loal, teavitab haigla pea- v&otilde;i &uuml;lemarst kohut tahtest olenematu ravi l&otilde;petamisest kirjalikult. </eesti>
<inglise>If treatment is provided pursuant to a court authorisation, the chief doctor of the hospital shall inform the court of discontinuation of involuntary treatment in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Tahtest olenematul ravil viibiva isikuga ei ole lubatud teha kliinilisi katseid, katsetada uusi ravimeid ega ravimeetodeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Persons in involuntary treatment shall not be subjected to clinical trials, testing of new medicinal products or treatment methods. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) J&auml;relevalvet tahtest olenematu ravi &uuml;le teostab Tervishoiuamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) The Health Care Board shall exercise supervision over involuntary treatment. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 50, 284) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.05.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 50, 284) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Ohjeldusmeetmete rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Use of means of restraint </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ohjeldusmeetmeid rakendatakse ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;irega isiku suhtes k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 11 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud asjaoludel, kui on otsene oht enesevigastuseks v&otilde;i v&auml;givallaks teiste isikute suhtes ja muud vahendid ohu k&otilde;rvaldamiseks ei ole osutunud k&uuml;llaldaseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Means of restraint are used with regard to persons with mental disorders in the circumstances provided for in subsection 11 (1) of this Act if there is an immediate danger of bodily harm to themselves or violence toward other persons and other measures for elimination of danger have been insufficient. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ohjeldusmeetmetena kasutatakse eraldamist ja fikseerimist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Isolation and physical restraint are used as means of restraint. </inglise>
<eesti>Eraldamine on isiku eralduspalatisse paigutamine ning seal meditsiinit&ouml;&ouml;taja j&auml;relevalve all kinnipidamine. </eesti>
<inglise>Isolation means placement of a person in an isolation room and detainment in that room under supervision of medical staff. </inglise>
<eesti>Fikseerimine on eralduspalatis meditsiinit&ouml;&ouml;taja j&auml;relevalve all mehaaniliste vahendite (rihmad, eririietus) kasutamine isiku tegutsemisvabaduse piiramiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Physical restraint means the use of mechanical means (straps, special clothing) in order to restrict the liberty of movement of a person in an isolation room under supervision of medical staff. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ohjeldusmeetmeid rakendatakse arsti otsusel, mis vormistatakse koos p&otilde;hjendusega ravidokumentides, ja nende rakendamine l&otilde;petatakse koheselt ohu m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Means of restraint are used on the basis of decisions of physicians which are documented in medical files with justifications, and their use is discontinued immediately after danger ceases to exist. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Ps&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiis ja kohtu poolt ps&uuml;hhiaatriahaiglasse paigutatud isiku ps&uuml;hhiaatriline ravi </eesti>
<inglise>Psychiatric Examinations and Psychiatric Treatment of Persons Placed in Psychiatric Hospital by Court </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtups&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiis </eesti>
<inglise>Forensic psychiatric examination </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kohtups&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiis m&auml;&auml;ratakse ja tehakse kriminaalmenetluse koodeksis (ENSV &Uuml;T 1961, 1, 4 ja lisa; RT I 2000, 56, 369; 75, lk 3296; 84, 533; 86, 542; 2001, 3, 9; 53, 306 ja 313) ja tsiviilkohtupidamise seadustikus (RT I 1993, 31/32, 538; 1994, 1, 5; 1995, 29, 358; 1996, 3, 57; 42, 811) kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Forensic psychiatric examination is ordered and carried out pursuant to the procedures established in the Code of Criminal Procedure (ENSV &Uuml;T (2) 1961, 1, 4 and lisa (3); RT I 2000, 56, 369; 75, p. 3296; 84, 533; 86, 542; 2001, 3, 9; 53, 306 and 313) and the Code of Civil Procedure (RT I 1993, 31/32, 538; 1994, 1, 5; 1995, 29, 358; 1996, 3, 57; 42, 811). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohtuniku loal v&otilde;i kohtum&auml;&auml;ruse alusel v&otilde;ib vabaduses viibiva kahtlustatava, s&uuml;&uuml;distatava v&otilde;i kohtualuse paigutada haigla ps&uuml;hhiaatriaosakonda kohtups&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiisi tegemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) With the authorisation of a judge or pursuant to a court ruling, a suspect, an accused person or an accused person under trial who is at large may be placed in the psychiatric department of a hospital in order that a forensic psychiatric examination may be carried out. </inglise>
<eesti>Ekspertiisi taotlenud ametiisik teavitab isiku haigla ps&uuml;hhiaatriaosakonda paigutamisest tema seaduslikku esindajat v&otilde;i l&auml;hedast inimest 72 tunni jooksul p&auml;rast kohtuniku loa k&auml;ttesaamist. </eesti>
<inglise>The official requesting such examination shall inform the legal representative or person close to the person that the person has been placed in the psychiatric department of a hospital within seventy-two hours after receipt of the authorisation of the judge. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kohtups&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiisid on ambulatoorsed ja statsionaarsed. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Forensic psychiatric examinations are outpatient or inpatient. </inglise>
<eesti>Ambulatoorne kohtups&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiis tehakse t&auml;htajaga kuni kaks n&auml;dalat, statsionaarne kohtups&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiis kuni kaks kuud. </eesti>
<inglise>Outpatient forensic psychiatric examinations are carried out within a period of up to two weeks and inpatient forensic examinations are carried out within a period of up to two months. </inglise>
<eesti>Erandjuhtudel pikendab kohus (kohtunik) kohtups&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiisi tegemist eksperdi taotlusel. </eesti>
<inglise>As an exception, a court (judge) shall extend the period for a forensic psychiatric examination at the request of an expert. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kohtups&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiisi teevad sellekohase tegevusloaga ps&uuml;hhiaatrid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Forensic psychiatric examinations are carried out by psychiatrists with appropriate activity licences. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaitsev&auml;eteenistuseks k&otilde;lblikkuse ps&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiis </eesti>
<inglise>Psychiatric examinations to determine fitness to serve in armed forces </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kaitsev&auml;eteenistuseks k&otilde;lblikkuse ps&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiis tehakse koosk&otilde;las kaitsev&auml;eteenistuse seadusega (RT I 1994, 23, 384; 1995, 18, 240; 62, 1056; 1996, 25, 519; 49, 953; 1997, 95/96, 1575; 1998, 57, 865; 1999, 10, 150; 25, 365) Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Psychiatric examinations to determine fitness to serve in the armed forces are carried out in accordance with the Armed Forces Service Act (RT I 1994, 23, 384; 1995, 18, 240; 62, 1056; 1996, 25, 519; 49, 953; 1997, 95/96, 1575; 1998, 57, 865; 1999, 10, 150; 25, 365) pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaitsev&auml;eteenistuseks k&otilde;lblikkuse ps&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiisile esitatavad n&otilde;uded kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The requirements set for psychiatric examinations to determine fitness to serve in the armed forces shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise ravi n&otilde;uded ja ps&uuml;hhiaatriahaigla t&ouml;&ouml;korraldus kohtu poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud meditsiinilise iseloomuga m&otilde;jutusvahendite kohaldamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for psychiatric treatment and procedure in psychiatric hospitals in administration of court ordered coercive treatment </inglise>
<eesti>Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise ravi n&otilde;uded ja ps&uuml;hhiaatriahaigla t&ouml;&ouml;korralduse kohtu poolt kriminaalkoodeksi (RT 1992, 20, 288; RT I 1999, 38, 485; 57, 595, 597 ja 598; 60, 616; 97, 859; 102, 907; 2000, 10, 55; 28, 167; 29, 173; 33, 193; 40, 247; 49, 301 ja 305; 54, 351; 57, 373; 58, 376; 84, 533; 92, 597; 104, 685; 2001, 21, 115 ja 116; 31, 174; 53, 306 ja 313) paragrahv 59 l&otilde;ike 1 alusel m&auml;&auml;ratud meditsiinilise iseloomuga m&otilde;jutusvahendite kohaldamisel ps&uuml;hhiaatriahaiglas kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The requirements for psychiatric treatment and the procedure in psychiatric hospitals for the administration of court ordered coercive treatment in psychiatric hospitals pursuant to subsection 59 (1) of the Criminal Code (RT 1992, 20, 288; RT I 1999, 38, 485; 57, 595 and 597, 598; 60, 616; 97, 859; 102, 907; 2000, 10, 55; 28, 167; 29, 173; 33, 193; 40, 247; 49, 301 and 305; 54, 351; 57, 373; 58, 376; 84, 533; 92, 597; 104, 685; 2001, 21, 115 and 116; 31, 174; 53, 306 and 313) shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Finantseerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Financing </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi finantseerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Financing of psychiatric care </inglise>
<eesti>Ps&uuml;hhiaatrilist abi finantseeritakse tervishoiukorralduse seaduses, Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses (RT 1991, 23, 272; RT I 1999, 7, 113; 29, 397; 2000, 57, 374; 84, 536; 102, 675; 2001, 42, 233; 47, 260), sotsiaalhoolekande seaduses ja k&auml;esolevas seaduses kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Psychiatric care is financed pursuant to the procedure established in the Health Care Administration Act, the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act (RT 1991, 23, 272; RT I 1999, 7, 113; 29, 397; 2000, 57, 374; 84, 536; 102, 675; 2001, 42, 233; 47, 260), the Social Welfare Act and this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigieelarvest finantseeritav ps&uuml;hhiaatriline abi, ravi ja ekspertiis </eesti>
<inglise>Psychiatric care, treatment and expert examinations financed from state budget </inglise>
<eesti>Ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmamata isikule antava v&auml;ltimatu ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise abi, ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;ire t&otilde;ttu vaeguriks tunnistatud isiku hooldamise ja taastusabi kulud, kohtups&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiisi ja kaitsev&auml;eteenistuseks k&otilde;lblikkuse ps&uuml;hhiaatriaekspertiisi tegemise ning kohtu poolt ps&uuml;hhiaatriahaiglasse paigutatud isiku ps&uuml;hhiaatrilise ravi kulud kaetakse riigieelarvest. </eesti>
<inglise>The expenses of the provision of emergency psychiatric care to persons who are not covered by health insurance, of care for and rehabilitation of persons who are declared disabled due to a mental disorder, expenses relating to carrying out forensic psychiatric examinations, to psychiatric examinations to determine fitness to serve in the armed forces and psychiatric treatment of persons committed to a psychiatric hospital by the courts shall be covered from the state budget. </inglise>
